<% content_for :title, "Review Link Unavailable" %>

<div class="review-access-state">
  <section class="review-access-panel" aria-labelledby="review-link-unavailable-title">
    <p class="review-access-kicker">Review Access</p>
    <p class="review-access-code">410 / LINK UNAVAILABLE</p>

    <h1 id="review-link-unavailable-title">This review link is no longer available.</h1>

    <p class="review-access-lead">
      This magic link is invalid, expired, or has already been used. Review links are intentionally
      time-limited and tied to a single review assignment.
    </p>

    <div class="review-access-section">
      <h2>What To Do Next</h2>
      <ul class="review-access-list">
        <li>Return to the original email and confirm you opened the most recent link.</li>
        <li>If the link has expired, request a new review email from HR or the cycle administrator.</li>
        <li>If you already submitted your review, no further action is required.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="review-access-note">
      <p>Security note: links are single-purpose and cannot be reused across different review assignments.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
